==English==
===Pronunciation===
nāv, {{IPAchar|/neɪv/}}, <tt>/neIv/</tt>

*Homophones: [[knave]]
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪv|-eɪv]]

===Etymology===
Ultimately from Latin [[navis]], ''ship'', via a Romance source.

===Noun===
'''nave''' (plural [[naves]])
#The middle or body of a church, extending from the [[transept]]s to the principal entrances.

====Translations====
*French: [[nef]]
*German: [[Schiff]]

===Etymology===
From Old English [[nafu]]. Cognates include Dutch [[naaf]] and German [[Nabe]].

===Noun===
'''nave''' (plural [[naves]])
#A [[hub]] of a [[wheel]] <!--as in "bowl the round nave" from Hamlet--->

